9 An Act relating to municipal zoning; defining terms;
prohibiting a municipal governing body from adopting
10 certain regulations; allowing a municipal governing
body to adopt certain regulations; providing for
11 codification; and providing an effective date.
12
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 43-117 of Title 11, unless there
17 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 A. As used in this section:
19 1. “Business” has the same meaning as that provided in Section
20 2001 of Title 18 of the Oklahoma Statutes;
21 2. “Home-based business” means a business that is operated:
22 a. on a residential property,
23 b. by the owner or tenant of such property, and
24 c. for the purpose of:
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB1519 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 (1) manufacturing, providing, or selling a lawful
2 good, or
3 (2) providing a lawful service;
4 3. “No-impact home-based business” means a home-based business
5 that:
6 a. has, at any time on the residential property where
7 such business is operated, a total number of
8 employees, clients, or patrons of such business that
9 does not exceed the occupancy limit for such property
10 established by municipal ordinance,
11 b. does not generate on-street parking or a substantial
12 increase in vehicular traffic in the surrounding area,
13 c. conducts business activities in a manner which
14 prevents the viewing of such activities from any
15 street or highway, and
16 d. does not substantially increase noise of the
17 surrounding area or otherwise violate any regulation
18 of noise established by municipal ordinance; and
19 4. “Short-term rental unit” means any residential dwelling, or
20 a portion of such dwelling, that is rented for a period of less than
21 thirty (30) consecutive days.
22 B. No municipal governing body may adopt or enforce any
23 ordinance, regulation, or measure that:
24
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB1519 SFLR Page 2
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 1. Prohibits the operation of a no-impact home-based business
2 within the limits of the municipality;
3 2. Requires a person operating a no-impact home-based business,
4 or owning the property where such business operates, to obtain a
5 license, permit, or any other form of approval to operate such
6 business; or
7 3. Requires a person operating a no-impact home-based business,
8 or owning the property where such business operates, to:
9 a. file for a zoning change allowing for a non-
10 residential use of such property, or
11 b. install a fire suppression system if the property
12 where such business operates exclusively consists of:
13 (1) a single-family detached residential structure,
14 or
15 (2) a multi-family residential structure with not
16 more than two residential units.
17 C. Except as provided for in subsection B of this section, a
18 municipal governing body may adopt or enforce an ordinance,
19 regulation, or measure that requires a no-impact home-based business
20 to:
21 1. Be in compliance with federal, state, and local law,
22 including:
23 a. municipal fire and building code, and
24 b. municipal regulations related to:
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB1519 SFLR Page 3
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 (1) health and sanitation,
2 (2) transportation or traffic control,
3 (3) solid or hazardous waste,
4 (4) pollution and noise control, or
5 (5) nuisance, as provided by Section 22-121 of Title
6 11 of the Oklahoma Statutes;
7 2. Be compatible with the residential use of the property where
8 such business is located;
9 3. Ensure that any business activities are secondary to the use
10 of such property as a dwelling; and
11 4. Not engage in:
12 a. the sale of alcohol or trafficking of illegal drugs,
13 b. the operation of a transitional living facility or
14 halfway house, as defined in Section 3-403 of Title
15 43A of the Oklahoma Statutes, or
16 c. the operation of a sexually oriented business, as
17 defined in Section 1040.55 of Title 21 of the Oklahoma
18 Statutes.
19 D. The provisions of this section shall not be construed as
20 prohibiting:
21 1. Any person from enforcing a rule or deed restriction imposed
22 by a homeowners’ association or by other private agreement;
23 2. A municipal governing body from adopting or enforcing an
24 ordinance regulating the operation of a short-term rental unit; or
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB1519 SFLR Page 4
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 3. A municipal governing body from carrying out its obligation
2 to ensure the public safety of the municipality.
3 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
4 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON LOCAL AND COUNTY GOVERNMENT
